SIMPLE: henna
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Henna
<hw>Hen"na</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Ar.
<ets>hinn⟦amac⟧</ets> alcanna (<spn>Lawsonia inermis</spn> syn.
<spn>Lawsonia alba</spn>). Cf. <er>Alcanna</er>, <er>Alkanet</er>,
<er>Orchanet</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A thorny tree or shrub of the
genus <gen>Lawsonia</gen> (<spn>Lawsonia alba</spn>). The fragrant white
blossoms are used by the Buddhists in religious ceremonies. The powdered
leaves furnish a red coloring matter used in the East to stain the nails
and fingers, the manes of horses, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Com.)</fld> <def>The leaves of the henna plant, or
a preparation or dyestuff made from them.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hennery</ent>⟦br⟧
